The hand just given also has another interesting point. If East had played the Ten of spades instead of the Ace on the first trick, South would have been put in a bad spot. If South thought East was deliberately holding back either the Ace or the King, he should duck, of course. However, if both the Ace and the King should be in the West hand, the duck will be a losing play as East can come through the Declarer twice.|
